    <title>Homework 9.4</title>

<exercisegroup cols = "2">
    <introduction><p>For Problems 1<ndash/>8, write the sum in expanded form.</p></introduction>

    <exercise number="1"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^{4} i^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>1^2+2^2+3^2+4^2</m>  </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="2"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^{3} (3i-2)}</m></statement></exercise>

    <exercise number="3"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{j=5}^{7} (j-2)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>3+4+5</m>  </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="4"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{j=2}^{6} (j^2+1)}</m></statement></exercise>

    <exercise number="5"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{4} k(k+1)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>1(2)+2(3)+3(4)+4(5)</m>  </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="6"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=2}^{6} \dfrac{k}{2}(k+1)}</m></statement></exercise>

    <exercise number="7"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{m=1}^{4} \dfrac{(-1)^m}{2^m}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{-1}{2}+\dfrac{1}{2^2}-\dfrac{1}{2^3}+\dfrac{1}{2^4}</m>  </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="8"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{m=3}^{5} \dfrac{(-1)^{m+1}}{m-2}}</m></statement></exercise>
</exercisegroup>

<exercisegroup cols = "2">
    <introduction><p>For Problems 9<ndash/>20, write the series using sigma notation.</p></introduction>

    <exercise number="9"><statement><m>1+3+5+7</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{4} (2k-1)}</m>  </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="10"><statement><m>2+4+6+8</m></statement></exercise> 

    <exercise number="11"><statement><m>5+5^3+5^5+5^7</m></statement>
        <answer> <m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{4} 5^{2k-1}}</m> </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="12"><statement><m>4^3+4^5+4^7+4^9+4^{11}</m></statement></exercise>

    <exercise number="13"><statement><m>1+4+9+16+25</m></statement>
        <answer> <m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{5} k^2}</m> </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="14"><statement><m>1+8+27+64+125</m></statement></exercise>

    <exercise number="15"><statement><m>\dfrac{1}{2}+\dfrac{2}{3}+\dfrac{3}{4}+\dfrac{4}{5}+\dfrac{5}{6}</m></statement>
    <answer> <m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{5} \dfrac{k}{k+1}}</m> </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="16"><statement><m>\dfrac{2}{1}+\dfrac{3}{2}+\dfrac{4}{3}+\dfrac{5}{4}+\dfrac{6}{5}</m></statement></exercise>

    <exercise number="17"><statement><m>\dfrac{1}{1}+\dfrac{2}{3}+\dfrac{3}{5}+\dfrac{4}{7}+\dfrac{5}{9}+\dfrac{6}{11}</m></statement>
    <answer> <m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{6} \dfrac{k}{2k-1}}</m> </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="18"><statement><m>\dfrac{3}{1}+\dfrac{5}{3}+\dfrac{7}{5}+\dfrac{9}{7}+\dfrac{11}{9}</m></statement></exercise>

    <exercise number="19"><statement><m>\dfrac{1}{1}+\dfrac{2}{2}+\dfrac{4}{3}+\dfrac{8}{4}+\cdots</m></statement>
    <answer><m> \displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \dfrac{2^{k-1}}{k}}</m> </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="20"><statement><m>\dfrac{1}{2}+\dfrac{3}{4}+\dfrac{9}{6}+\dfrac{27}{8}+\cdots</m></statement></exercise>
    </exercisegroup>

<exercisegroup cols = "2">
    <introduction><p>For Problems 21<ndash/>40, identify the series as arithmetic, geometric or neither, then evaluate it.</p></introduction>

    <exercise number="21"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^{6} (i^2+1)}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Neither; 97</p>  </answer></exercise>

    <exercise number="22"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^{5} 3i^2}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="23"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{j=1}^{4} \dfrac{1}{j}}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Neither; <m>\dfrac{25}{12}</m></p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="24"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{j=0}^{4} \dfrac{2}{j+1}}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="25"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{100} 1}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Neither; 100</p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="26"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{300} 3}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="27"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{q=1}^{20} 3^q}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Geometric; <m>5,230,176,600</m></p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="28"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{p=1}^{30} 2^p}</m>
</statement></exercise>

<exercise number="29"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{200} k}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Atithmetic; <m>20,100</m></p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="30"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=1}^{150} k}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="31"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{n=1}^{6} n^3}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Neither; 441</p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="32"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{n=1}^{7} n^2}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="33"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{n=0}^{30} (3n-1)}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Arithemetic; 1364</p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="34"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=0}^{20} (5k+2)}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="35"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{k=0}^{25} (5-2k)}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Arithmetic; <m>-520</m></p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="36"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{p=0}^{15} (2-3p)}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="37"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{j=0}^{10} 5\cdot 2^j}</m></statement>
    <answer><p>Geometric; <m>24,414,062</m></p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="38"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{j=0}^{10} 3\cdot 2^j}</m></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="39"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{m=0}^{12} 50(1.08)^m}</m></statement>
<answer><p>Geometric; <m>104.76</m></p>  </answer></exercise>

<exercise number="40"><statement><m>\displaystyle{\sum_{m=0}^{18} 300(1.12)^m}</m></statement></exercise>
</exercisegroup>

<exercisegroup cols = "2"><introduction><p>For Problems 41<ndash/>48, </p><p><ol label = "a">
